	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64733378"><p><div class="quote"><p>So, professor Tannenbaum has been right all along?</p></div><p>No, not really.</p><p>Microkernels have advantages, and real-time is one of them.</p><p>But they also have drawbacks, like networking and file system performance, which matter more to most people most of the time.</p><p>For a desktop or server OS, monolithic is generally better and has won in the marketplace.</p></div>
	</div>

